Arrays Intro

It is a reference type data used for storing similar -multiple data in a single variable


How to create an array?
1. using brackets notation [] known as array literal - MOSTLY PREFERRED
 const array = []; // empty array
const ar2 = [1,10,7]; // numbers array
const arr3 = ['John, Alex']; string array

2. using new array [] constructor.
const arr4 = new Array(1,2,3); // number array 
const arr5 = new Array(); // empty array 

the typeof operator for array is object 
console.log(typeof arr1); // object 
console.log(typeof arr6); // object

Array Indices- INDEXES
Each array element is stored within an index starting from 0
You can use the index to access updates, delete, manipulate data

HOW TO CHECK THE LENGTH OF AN ARRAY?
length property is used to check how many elements exist within an array
console.log(arr5.length); // 

to get the last element in an array
length -1

example: arr[arr.length -1];
 
 
 **typically use const keyword with arrays





